premise_source_doc_sentence: Amerigo Vespucci  (  -LSB- ameˈriːɡo vesˈputtʃi -RSB- ; March 9 , 1454February 22 , 1512  )  was an Italian explorer , financier , navigator and cartographer who first demonstrated that Brazil and the West Indies did not represent Asia 's eastern outskirts as initially conjectured from Columbus ' voyages , but instead constituted an entirely separate landmass hitherto unknown to Old Worlders .
Colloquially referred to as the New World , this second super continent came to be termed `` Americas '' , deriving its name from Americus , the Latin version of Vespucci 's first name .
Ponte Amerigo Vespucci is a bridge over the Arno River in Florence , Italy and named after Florence-born explorer Amerigo Vespucci .
Among his crew was a Florentine resident in Seville , Amerigo Vespucci .
It is possible that the Aurora islands were `` discovered '' by Amerigo Vespucci in his 1501/1502 voyage with a Portuguese expedition .
It joins the Lungarno Amerigo Vespucci to the Lungarno Soderini .

The probability is confirmed by Vice-Admiral Ernesto Basilico in The Third Voyage of Amerigo Vespucci  (  Buenos Aires , 1967  )  and by Lt-Cdr Barreiro Meiro  (  General Journal of Navy , October 1968 , Madrid  )  .
